Example 6

Express the first quantity as a percentage of the second: 45 minutes, 3 hours

Solution:

$\frac{45 \text{ minutes}}{3 \text{ hours}} = \frac{45 \text{ minutes}}{3 \times 60 \text{ minutes}}$ {write as a fraction with the same units}
$= \frac{45}{180} \times 100\%$ {$100\% = 1$}
$= 25\%$

Example 10

(a) Find 100% of a quantity if 6% of the quantity is 42.

(b) Find 71% of a quantity if 40% of the quantity is 480.

Solutions:

(a) $6\%$ corresponds to 42
$\therefore$ $1\%$ corresponds to 7 {dividing by 6}
$\therefore$ $100\%$ corresponds to 700 {multiplying by 100}

(b) $40\%$ corresponds to 480
$\therefore$ $1\%$ corresponds to 12 {dividing by 40}
$\therefore$ $71\%$ corresponds to 852 {multiplying by 71}
